# Trivy ignore file (referenced by .github/actions/iac-checks via TRIVY_IGNOREFILE).
# Reviewed, deliberately-accepted misconfiguration findings. IDs only match the resources
# they describe, so this is safe to share across all infra template scans.
#
# Azure customer-provisioning template — two network-restriction checks that cannot be
# default-on without breaking provisioning: the alethia runner applies these from OUTSIDE
# Azure (Hetzner fleet), so a default-Deny key-vault ACL or an IP-locked AKS API server
# would block the runner's own data-plane / control-plane access. Left customer-configurable
# per environment. (RBAC — AVD-AZU-0042 — IS genuinely fixed in the AKS module.)
AVD-AZU-0013
AVD-AZU-0041

# connector-assets bucket is INTENTIONALLY public-read: it serves the CloudFormation
# template + Cloud Shell setup scripts, and AWS CFN quick-create requires a public
# S3-hosted URL. The public-access-block "should block public" checks and the CMK
# encryption check are therefore by design (public, non-secret files). Also covers the
# tofu-state bucket's AVD-AWS-0132: SSE-S3 (AES256) is the standard baseline for OpenTofu
# state and the bucket is already access-controlled; a CMK on a bucket shared by every
# stack is disproportionate. (Moved here from infra/.trivy.yaml's exclude:, which trivy
# does not honor — .trivyignore/TRIVY_IGNOREFILE is the mechanism that actually works.)
AVD-AWS-0086
AVD-AWS-0087
AVD-AWS-0091
AVD-AWS-0093
AVD-AWS-0094
AVD-AWS-0132

# cp-gcp control-plane box (infra/cp-gcp) INTENTIONALLY has a public IP. It is the single
# ephemeral external IP the VM needs for EGRESS (image pulls, git clone, dialing the Cloudflare
# Tunnel out) — inbound web is firewalled shut (ingress is tunnel-only) and inbound SSH is
# IAP-gated (tcp/22 from 35.235.240.0/20 only). A Cloud NAT gateway would remove the IP but cost
# ~10x for a single box, so the egress-only public IP is the cost-correct choice. This mirrors the
# accepted cp-hetzner posture (its box also has a public IP; Trivy simply has no hcloud checks).
AVD-GCP-0031

# cp-aws control-plane box (infra/cp-aws) needs UNRESTRICTED EGRESS. The single box pulls container
# images (GHCR + many CDN IPs), git-clones, and dials the Cloudflare Tunnel + SSM Session Manager out
# — all to large, dynamic IP ranges that cannot be pinned to CIDRs without breaking updates/pulls.
# Inbound is fully closed (the SG has NO ingress; web is tunnel-fronted, SSH is SSM), so the box is an
# origin, not a pivot — egress-all is the accepted, cost-correct posture for a single self-contained VM.
AVD-AWS-0104
